Definition: concerned with or comprehending only what is apparent or obvious
Example: not deep or penetrating emotionally or intellectually; superficial similarities; a superficial mind; his thinking was superficial and fuzzy; superficial knowledge; the superficial report didn't give the true picture; only superficial differences
Synonyms: noun, attribute, superficiality, PROFOUND, CARELESS, FRIVOLOUS, OUTWARD, concerned, with, or, comprehending, only, what, is, apparent, obvious, not, deep, penetrating, emotionally, intellectually, superficial, similarities, a, mind, his, thinking, was, and, fuzzy, knowledge, the, report, didn, t, give, true, picture, differences
Category: adj.all
